    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-03T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="812"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d812">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/10241</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Agent at Corfu</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DHP1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Corfu</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-03T16:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 4, 9.32 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 29th communicated to Premier who replies expressing profound appreciation
                    and certainty that with the help of the Government of the United States and its
                    sympathy, hour approaches of complete fulfillment of national aspirations of his
                    people which is one in fact although having three names. <persName
                        corresp="#p_TA2">Trumbitch</persName>, President of Southern Slav Committee,
                    also expresses deep appreciation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DHP1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
